I&#39;ve also faced the same issue, but with Gradle. For me, the problem was with the following instructions 

    debug {
        testCoverageEnabled true
    }
which I&#39;ve added in accordance with one tutorial. It also instruments classes (as Jacoco does) and thus the exceptions are thrown. 

Removing this instruction solved the problem for me.

This works for me

    debug {
        // disable testCoverage to fix Jacoco instrument error
        testCoverageEnabled false
    }

